.TH "configfs_register_default_group" 9 "configfs_register_default_group" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
configfs_register_default_group \- allocates and registers a child group
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct config_group *" configfs_register_default_group
.BI "(struct config_group *parent_group "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "const struct config_item_type *item_type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent_group" 12
parent group
.IP "name" 12
child group name
.IP "item_type" 12
child item type description
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
boilerplate to allocate and register a child group with its parent. We need
kzalloc'ed memory because child's default_group is initially empty.
.SH "RETURN"
allocated config group or \fBERR_PTR\fP on error
